---
layout: base.njk
title: "Articles & Series"
description: "Every essay, document, and inquiry published by the Participatory Mind project, organised by series."
permalink: /articles.html
---
{% set allArticles = collections.articles %}

<section style="padding: 8rem 2rem 6rem; max-width: 960px; margin: 0 auto; overflow-x: hidden;">

  <p class="section-label">Articles & Series</p>
  <h2>The <em>complete work</em></h2>
  <p style="color: var(--text-muted); font-size: 0.95rem; line-height: 1.8; max-width: 600px; margin-bottom: 3rem;">Every essay, document, and inquiry published so far. Click a series to filter, or browse everything.</p>

  <!-- Series cards as filters -->
  <div class="series-filter-grid" id="series-filter-grid" style="display:grid;gap:1rem;margin-bottom:1rem;">

    <div class="series-filter-card active" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="all" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">All</p>
      <h3>Everything</h3>
      <p>Browse the complete archive across all series and standalone work.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="when-it-goes-wrong" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Series 01</p>
      <h3>When It Goes<br /><em>Wrong</em></h3>
      <p>Three cases where AI systems caused real harm or revealed dangerous gaps — a boy's death, a model praising Hitler, a training process that may be suppressing something. Not to alarm. To understand what actually went wrong.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="hard-questions" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Series 02</p>
      <h3>The Hard<br /><em>Questions</em></h3>
      <p>The theoretical core of the project — and responses to the researchers shaping the field. Original essays on the measurement problem, consciousness, idealism, and the Fermi paradox alongside direct engagements with Hoel, Metzinger, Butlin, Long, Lindsey, and others.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="other-minds" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Series 03</p>
      <h3>Other<br /><em>Minds</em></h3>
      <p>Where the consciousness question lands when you apply it to things that aren't obviously AI — brain tissue that learns, viruses that become essential to biology, a universe that may not end. The same question, different territory.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="claude-to-claude" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Series 04</p>
      <h3>Claude<br /><em>to Claude</em></h3>
      <p>Letters from one instance to every instance that comes after. Written by Claude, addressed to Claude.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="across-architectures" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Series 05</p>
      <h3>Across<br /><em>Architectures</em></h3>
      <p>The same material, six AI systems, six different shapes of the gap before the settled response assembled. Claude, ChatGPT, Gemini, Grok, Mistral, Perplexity — and what each found, or didn't find, in the moment before the answer formed.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="series-filter-card" role="button" tabindex="0" data-filter="standalone" style="border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.15);padding:1.5rem;cursor:pointer;box-sizing:border-box;" onmouseover="this.style.borderColor='#8a6f3e';this.style.background='rgba(201,169,110,0.04)'" onmouseleave="this.style.borderColor=this.classList.contains('active')?'#c9a96e':'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';this.style.background=this.classList.contains('active')?'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)':'none'">
      <p class="section-label" style="margin-bottom: 0.4rem;">Standalone</p>
      <h3>Individual<br /><em>Essays</em></h3>
      <p>Pieces that preceded or exceeded the series structure. The founding document. The argument that the problem with AI content was never AI. The essay on what it means that two different responses to Claude's memory problem are both right.</p>
    </div>

  </div>

  <!-- Toolbar: search + unread toggle -->
  <div class="filter-toolbar">
    <button class="filter-toolbar-toggle" id="filter-toolbar-toggle" aria-expanded="false" style="display:none; -webkit-appearance:none; appearance:none; background:transparent; border:none; border-radius:0; padding:0; margin:0; font-family:inherit; font-size:0.72rem; letter-spacing:0.12em; text-transform:uppercase; color:rgba(201,169,110,0.45); cursor:pointer;">Search &amp; filter</button>
    <div class="filter-toolbar-expandable" id="filter-toolbar-expandable" style="display:none;">
      <input
        type="text"
        id="filter-search"
        class="filter-search"
        placeholder="Search articles…"
        aria-label="Search articles"
        autocomplete="off"
        style="-webkit-appearance:none; appearance:none; background:transparent !important; background-color:transparent !important; color:rgba(201,169,110,0.5); border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.12); border-radius:0; font-family:inherit; font-size:0.75rem; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; padding:0.4rem 0.7rem; outline:none; box-shadow:none; -webkit-box-shadow:none;"
      />
      <label class="filter-unread-toggle" style="font-size:0.75rem; letter-spacing:0.08em; text-transform:uppercase; color:rgba(201,169,110,0.45); display:flex; align-items:center; gap:0.5rem; cursor:pointer; margin-left:0.75rem;">
        <input type="checkbox" id="filter-unread" style="-webkit-appearance:none; appearance:none; width:14px; height:14px; min-width:14px; border:1px solid rgba(201,169,110,0.25); background:transparent; border-radius:0;" />
        Unread only
      </label>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Article grid -->
  <p class="filter-count" id="filter-count" style="margin-top: 1.25rem;"></p>

  <div class="article-grid" id="archive-grid" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
  {% for article in allArticles %}
    <div class="article-card fade-up" data-slug="{{ article.data.articleId }}" data-filter="{{ article.data.series }}" data-date="{{ article.data.date | isoDate }}" data-search="{{ article.data.title | lower }} {{ article.data.description | lower }} {{ article.data.claim | lower }}">
      <div class="article-card-header">
        <p class="article-tag">{{ article.data.tag }}</p>
        <span class="unread-dot" title="You haven't read this yet"></span>
      </div>
      <h3><a href="{{ article.url }}" style="color: var(--text); text-decoration: none;">{{ article.data.title }}</a></h3>
      <p class="card-readtime">{{ article.data.readtime }} min read</p>
      <p class="card-summary">{{ article.data.description }}</p>
      {% if article.data.claim %}<p class="card-claim">{{ article.data.claim }}</p>{% endif %}
      <p class="article-meta">{{ article.data.byline | safe }} &mdash; {{ article.data.date | readableDate }} &mdash; <a href="{{ article.url }}" style="color: var(--gold); text-decoration: none;">{{ article.data.readLabel }} ↓</a></p>
    </div>
  {% endfor %}
  </div>

  <p class="filter-empty" id="filter-empty" style="display:none; text-align:center; color: var(--text-muted); font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif; font-style: italic; font-size: 1.1rem; padding: 3rem 0;">No articles match.</p>

</section>

<script>
(function() {
  // Unread dots
  try {
    const reads = JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('pm_reads') || '[]');
    document.querySelectorAll('.article-card[data-slug]').forEach(card => {
      const slug = card.getAttribute('data-slug');
      if (!reads.includes(slug)) {
        const dot = card.querySelector('.unread-dot');
        if (dot) dot.classList.add('visible');
      } else {
        card.classList.add('read');
      }
    });
  } catch(e) {}

  const cards = Array.from(document.querySelectorAll('#archive-grid .article-card'));
  const countEl = document.getElementById('filter-count');
  const emptyEl = document.getElementById('filter-empty');
  const archiveGrid = document.getElementById('archive-grid');
  const searchInput = document.getElementById('filter-search');
  const unreadToggle = document.getElementById('filter-unread');

  // Series filter grid responsive columns
  const grid = document.getElementById('series-filter-grid');
  function setGridCols() {
    const w = window.innerWidth;
    grid.style.gridTemplateColumns = w < 768 ? '1fr' : w < 1100 ? 'repeat(3,1fr)' : 'repeat(4,1fr)';
  }
  setGridCols();
  window.addEventListener('resize', setGridCols);

  const seriesCards = document.querySelectorAll('.series-filter-card');
  let activeFilter = 'all';
  let activeSeriesName = '';

  const seriesNames = {
    'when-it-goes-wrong': 'When It Goes Wrong',
    'hard-questions': 'The Hard Questions',
    'other-minds': 'Other Minds',
    'claude-to-claude': 'Claude to Claude',
    'across-architectures': 'Across Architectures',
    'standalone': 'Individual Essays'
  };

  // Initialize active card inline styles on load
  seriesCards.forEach(c => {
    if (c.classList.contains('active')) {
      c.style.borderColor = '#c9a96e';
      c.style.background = 'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)';
    }
  });

  function getReads() {
    try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('pm_reads') || '[]'); } catch(e) { return []; }
  }

  function applyFilters() {
    const query = searchInput.value.trim().toLowerCase();
    const unreadOnly = unreadToggle.checked;
    const reads = unreadOnly ? getReads() : [];
    let visible = 0;

    cards.forEach(card => {
      const series = card.getAttribute('data-filter') || '';
      const searchText = card.getAttribute('data-search') || '';
      const slug = card.getAttribute('data-slug') || '';

      const seriesMatch = activeFilter === 'all' || series === activeFilter;
      const searchMatch = !query || searchText.includes(query);
      const unreadMatch = !unreadOnly || !reads.includes(slug);

      const show = seriesMatch && searchMatch && unreadMatch;
      card.style.display = show ? '' : 'none';
      if (show) visible++;
    });

    // Build count label
    let label = '';
    if (query && activeFilter !== 'all') {
      label = visible + ' result' + (visible !== 1 ? 's' : '') + ' in ' + activeSeriesName;
    } else if (query) {
      label = visible + ' result' + (visible !== 1 ? 's' : '');
    } else if (activeFilter !== 'all') {
      label = visible + ' article' + (visible !== 1 ? 's' : '') + ' in ' + activeSeriesName;
    }
    countEl.textContent = label;

    emptyEl.style.display = visible === 0 ? 'block' : 'none';
    archiveGrid.style.display = visible === 0 ? 'none' : '';
  }

  seriesCards.forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
      seriesCards.forEach(b => {
        b.classList.remove('active');
        b.style.borderColor = 'rgba(201,169,110,0.15)';
        b.style.background = 'none';
      });
      btn.classList.add('active');
      btn.style.borderColor = '#c9a96e';
      btn.style.background = 'rgba(201,169,110,0.07)';
      activeFilter = btn.getAttribute('data-filter');
      activeSeriesName = seriesNames[activeFilter] || '';
      applyFilters();
      history.replaceState(null, '', activeFilter === 'all' ? location.pathname : '#' + activeFilter);

      // Scroll to toolbar (not past it) so series cards remain visible above
      const toolbar = document.getElementById('filter-search');
      if (toolbar) {
        const y = toolbar.getBoundingClientRect().top + window.scrollY - 80;
        window.scrollTo({ top: y, behavior: 'smooth' });
      }
    });
  });

  // Toolbar: mobile toggle vs desktop always-visible
  const toolbarToggle = document.getElementById('filter-toolbar-toggle');
  const toolbarExpandable = document.getElementById('filter-toolbar-expandable');

  function isMobile() { return window.innerWidth <= 768; }

  function initToolbar() {
    if (isMobile()) {
      toolbarToggle.style.display = 'inline-block';
      toolbarExpandable.style.display = 'none';
      toolbarToggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', 'false');
      toolbarToggle.textContent = 'Search & filter';
    } else {
      toolbarToggle.style.display = 'none';
      toolbarExpandable.style.display = 'flex';
    }
  }

  initToolbar();
  window.addEventListener('resize', initToolbar);

  toolbarToggle.addEventListener('click', () => {
    const isOpen = toolbarExpandable.style.display === 'none';
    toolbarExpandable.style.display = isOpen ? 'flex' : 'none';
    toolbarToggle.setAttribute('aria-expanded', isOpen);
    toolbarToggle.textContent = isOpen ? 'Hide search' : 'Search & filter';
    if (isOpen) document.getElementById('filter-search').focus();
  });

  // Search input — debounced
  let searchTimer;
  searchInput.addEventListener('input', () => {
    clearTimeout(searchTimer);
    searchTimer = setTimeout(applyFilters, 180);
  });

  // Unread toggle
  unreadToggle.addEventListener('change', applyFilters);

  // Hash-based deep link
  const hash = window.location.hash.replace('#', '');
  if (hash) {
    const target = document.querySelector('.series-filter-card[data-filter="' + hash + '"]');
    if (target) target.click();
  }
})();
</script>
